snippet.textDisplay:
Always did like the idea of Anakin being a Michael Corleone (Godfather) type character whose fall from grace was like a Shakesperian tragedy.
A man who grew into being a strong leader who gained power in order to protect those he cared about. Dragged into a war that cost many lives. A quest for power and control to end the suffering and to destroy his enemies becoming the very thing that pushed away those he fought to protect, ending up alone in his rage and regret.
